      "source": [
        "## **1. Fibonacci number**\n",
        "Your goal in this problem is to implement an efficient algorithm for computing\n",
        "Fibonacci numbers.\n",
        "### **Problem Description**\n",
        "**Task.**  Given an integer *n*, find the *n*th Fibonacci number *$F_n$*.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input Format.** The input consists of a single integer *n*.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Constraints.** 0 ≤ *n* ≤ 45.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Output Format.** Output *$F_n$*.\n",
        "### **Sample 1**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        " 10\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "55\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Code**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "hgpsBfzTpfhN",
        "outputId": "10c419cf-4d73-43ca-ac0f-44410442380a"
      },
      "source": [
        "%%writefile fibonacci.py\n",
        "import array as arr\n",
        "\n",
        "n = int(input())\n",
        "f = arr.array(\"i\", [0, 1])\n",
        "x = 2\n",
        "for i in range(2, n+1):\n",
        "    f.append(f[x-1]+f[x-2])\n",
        "    x = x+1\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f[n])"
      ],
      "execution_count": 1,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Writing fibonacci.py\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
        }
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "## **2. Last Digit of a Large Fibonacci Number**\n",
        "Your goal in this problem is to find the last digit of n-th Fibonacci number. Recall that Fibonacci numbers grow exponentially fast.\n",
        "### **Problem Description**\n",
        "**Task.**  Given an integer *n*, find the last digit of the *n*th Fibonacci number *$F_n$* (that is, *$F_n$* mod 10).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input Format.** The input consists of a single integer *n*.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Constraints.** 0 ≤ *n* ≤ $10^7$.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Output Format.** Output the last digit of *$F_n$*.\n",
        "### **Sample 1**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "3\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "2\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Sample 2**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "331\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "9\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Sample 3**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "327305\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "5\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Code**"
      ]
    },

          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "a745IUUypeBc",
        "outputId": "90f1c6db-7069-4b51-9889-e35f5f807e48"
      },
      "source": [
        "%%writefile lastfibonacci.py\n",

        "\n",
        "n = int(input())\n",

        "x = 2\n",
        "for i in range(2, n+1):\n",
        "    f.append((f[x-1]+f[x-2])%10)\n",
        "    x = x+1\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f[n])"

      "source": [
        "## **3.Greatest Common Divisor**\n",
        "The greatest common divisor GCD(a, b) of two non-negative integers a and b\n",
        "(which are not both equal to 0) is the greatest integer d that divides both a and b.\n",
        "Your goal in this problem is to implement the Euclidean algorithm for computing\n",
        "the greatest common divisor.\n",
        "\n",
        "Efficient algorithm for computing the greatest common divisor is an important\n",
        "basic primitive of commonly used cryptographic algorithms like RSA.\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Problem Description**\n",
        "**Task.**  Given two integers a and b, find their greatest common divisor.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input Format.** The two integers a, b are given in the same line separated by space.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Constraints.** 1 ≤ a,b ≤ $2*10^9$.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Output Format.** Output GCD(a,b).\n",
        "### **Sample 1**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "18 35\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "1\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Sample 2**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "28851538 1183019\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "17657\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Code**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "-FdTtLVApA60",
        "outputId": "9b5aca7a-228a-41e4-aff8-68bbf9077d8a"
      },
      "source": [
        "%%writefile gcd.py\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "\n",
        "def gcd(a, b):\n",
        "    current_gcd = a % b\n",
        "    if (current_gcd != 0):\n",
        "      return gcd(b,current_gcd)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "      return b\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    tokens = input().split()\n",
        "    a = int(tokens[0])\n",
        "    b = int(tokens[1])\n",
        "    print(gcd(a, b))"
      ],
      "execution_count": 24,
      "outputs": [

          "output_type": "stream",

            "Overwriting gcd.py\n"

    {

      "source": [
        "## **4. Least Common Multiple**\n",
        "The least common multiple of two positive integers a and b is the least positive\n",
        "integer m that is divisible by both a and b.\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Problem Description**\n",
        "**Task.**  Given two integers a and b, find their least common multiple.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input Format.** The two integers a and b are given in the same line separated by space.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Constraints.** 1 ≤ a,b ≤ $10^7$.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Output Format.** Output the least common multiple of a and b.\n",
        "### **Sample 1**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "6 8\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "24\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Sample 2**\n",
        "Input:\n",
        "\n",
        "761457 614573\n",
        "\n",
        "Output: \n",
        "\n",
        "467970912861\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Code**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "xS_iqf8Upejt",
        "outputId": "92549075-a924-488f-e358-b90fe3bcaf9a"
      },
      "source": [
        "%%writefile lcm.py\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "\n",
        "def gcd_naive(a, b):\n",
        "    current_gcd = 1\n",
        "    if(a>=b):\n",
        "        a_curr = a\n",
        "        b_curr = b\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        a_curr = b\n",
        "        b_curr = a\n",
        "    if(a==1 or b==1 or a==b):\n",
        "        return b_curr\n",
        "\n",
        "    if((a_curr%b_curr)==0):\n",
        "        return b_curr\n",
        "\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        current_gcd=a_curr%b_curr\n",
        "        a_curr = b_curr\n",
        "        b_curr = current_gcd\n",
        "        if ( a_curr%b_curr == 0 ):\n",
        "            break\n",
        "\n",
        "    return b_curr\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    tokens = input().split()\n",
        "    a = int(tokens[0])\n",
        "    b = int(tokens[1])\n",
        "    mcd=gcd_naive(a,b)\n",
        "    print(int(a*b/mcd))"
      ],
      "execution_count": 30,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Overwriting lcm.py\n"
          ],
          "name": "stdout"
